702925f-a.title: Brooklyn: 92nd Street (East) - Schenck Avenue
702925f-a.text:
East 92nd Street, south from Schenck Ave., showing a very old frame
shack and beer garden in front of coaster in Golden City Park, Canarsie.
July 6, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.

706624f-b.title: Brooklyn: Schenck Avenue - 92nd Street (East)
706624f-b.text:
9217 Schenck Avenue, north side, between East 92nd and
East 93rd Streets, viewing toward the latter and showing Bill's
O1d Homestead Beer Garden. Here Billy Ray for more than thirty
years operated a bar known as the "madhouse," because of electri-
cal gadgets that shocked customers when they picked up their
change or sst on certain chairs. The house, which was formerly
three stories high, was practically ramed by fire in 1933.
It was later demolished to make way for the construction of
the Belt Parkway.
View 2 is across East 92nd Street.
July 6, 1933
Views 1,2
P. L. iperr
